      "role": "user",
      "content": "but i didnt lose my password or anything. i still have full access to my accounts. it just feels different... like i'm watching a script of myself being played out by something else. if it's not a human hacker, wouldn't a sophisticated enough ai be able to just scrape my old writing and start mimicking my personality perfectly? like it's not an \"attack\", it's more like a digital copy has just replaced the original? it feels so much more real than just a standard hack.",
